# rustc-1.91.1.answers — byte-seal pins for packages/rustc-1.91.1.
#
# STATUS: UNPINNED.  This rung is GREEN, not SEALED.  Do not describe it as sealed anywhere.
#
# SELF-ARMING, exactly like packages/mrustc-rustc-1.90.0/rustc-1.90.0.answers.  The seal at the
# bottom of build.sh (P6) greps for `^<64 hex>  ` and, the moment one such line is present, runs
# `sha256sum -c` FAIL-SHUT from ${OUTPUT_DIR}.  Sealing this rung is a DATA edit, not a code edit.
#
# ── TO SHIP THE SEAL ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This file is NOT currently wired as a Local build_dep, so build.sh prints "NOT SEALED" and
# continues.  To arm it after TWO independent CS builds have produced byte-identical output:
#   1. add  `{ file = "rustc-1.91.1.answers" } | Local,`  to build.ncl's build_deps.
#   2. cd ${OUTPUT_DIR} && sha256sum usr/lib/rustc-1.91.1/bin/rustc \
#                                    usr/lib/rustc-1.91.1/bin/cargo
#   3. paste below, uncommented, in `sha256sum` format (TWO spaces between sha and path).
#   4. re-run.  Any drift now aborts the build.
#
# ── ⚠ DO NOT EXPECT THIS TO SEAL ON THE FIRST TRY, AND DO NOT TREAT THAT AS A BUG ────────────
# Known nondeterminism surface at this scope, none of it addressed yet (chasing it before the rung
# is even green would be premature):
#   - LLVM version-control rev ... external llvm-config is fixed, but rustc bakes an LLVM VC-rev
#                                  string; if it drifts, the driver hash drifts.
#   - cargo -Cmetadata hashes ... the workspace crates each have their own -Cmetadata surface.
#   - std debuginfo paths ....... Rust debuginfo may carry the build root (see P4's sweep).
# A second build here costs HOURS, not seconds, so build.sh does NOT attempt an in-build
# determinism proof.  Two-run comparison here means two CS builds, not one build doing it twice.
#
# ── WHAT TO PIN, AND WHAT NOT TO ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PIN: bin/rustc and bin/cargo — the two real ELF artifacts (contrast RUNG 1, whose bin/rustc was
#      a regenerated shell wrapper, so it pinned bin/rustc_binary instead; x.py bakes a real ELF
#      here, so bin/rustc IS the artifact to pin).
# DO NOT PIN:
#   - lib/rustlib/** ......... hundreds of .rlib files; pinning them adds seal churn without
#                              adding evidence, and they are covered transitively by the two
#                              binaries above being byte-identical.
#   - BUILDINFO .............. constants only, already covered by its inputs.
#
# ── ⚠ THE ANCHOR ITSELF IS NOT SEALED ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# packages/mrustc ships `# UNPINNED` mrustc.answers, so this whole chain is GREEN, not byte-SEALED.
# Sealing packages/mrustc (2 builds) benefits every rung and should be done independently.
#
# UNPINNED
# usr/lib/rustc-1.91.1/bin/rustc
# usr/lib/rustc-1.91.1/bin/cargo
